"Greenverz, tropical monsoon climates Forest Department nurseries, Indian native plant suppliers"}, {"name": "Malabar Chestnut (Pachira)", "slug": "malabar-chestnut-pachira", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 4, "origin": "Central/South America, widely grown in India including tropical monsoon climates, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu (Western Ghats)", "traits": "Evergreen tropical tree (up to 50 ft), glossy dark green leaves, spectacular white flowers, semi-deciduous", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good tropical producer", "growing_notes": "Species: Pachira insignis/glabra (Malvaceae family). EXCELLENT FOR tropical monsoon climates/tropical monsoon climates. Grown extensively in Western Ghats of tropical monsoon climates, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu. Perfectly adapted to warm tropical climate with plenty of rainfall - ideal for monsoon regions. Best harvested in dry season (ripe fruits). Well-suited to Tropical monsoon conditions. Requires warm climate, can tolerate some frost. Prefers full sun to partial shade. Well-drained soil essential. Used for desserts, snacks. Quality nuts have glossy bright-brown color. Can be stored 2 months cool/dry, or frozen 6 months. Ornamental value (beautiful flowers). Seeds raw not recommended (prepare first).", "availability": "tropical monsoon climates nurseries, Western Ghats plant suppliers, tropical nurseries throughout India"}, {"name": "2. Indian Chestnut (Sterculia foetida) - Native Kerala species", "slug": "2-indian-chestnut-sterculia-foetida-native-kerala-species", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 5, "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "3. Malabar Chestnut (Pachira) - Western Ghats cultivation", "slug": "3-malabar-chestnut-pachira-western-ghats-cultivation", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 6, "origin": "", "traits":